<br>
(( the letter is written on decent paper, not high quality velium or anything silly ))<br>
<br>
To the Lady Ankhami Vlos`dAthiak<br>
<br>
  Lady, I regret to inform you .. but it's come to my attention that you're currently holding my older brother as a slave. I'm quite perturbed at such and action and wish to have him returned to our family.<br>
<br>
  As such I see three options, First the family could  refund you your purchase price, I'm sure if we  sold grand mothers jewelry, and a few of the cattle we might have enough to do this. Second if you were to require a servant, I could serve some of his tenure, perhaps a year or so, to allow him the time he needs to straighten up the farm, also I could serve you during, the planting and harvesting seasons after that. Third of course, and something that I have considered is to  just do violence to you, then steal my brother back from you.<br>
<br>
 The latter option I rather dislike thinking about, but if such an action is required, then so be it.<br>
<br>
 Lady I do look forward to a speedy answer, else I shall have to take a more direct route to freeing my brother. I would hope this can be worked out in an peaceful manner.<br>
<br>
Tullari Har'Genath<br>
Adept of the Whistling Fist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ankhami>Ankhami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Priestess of the Father</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(7/5/03 9:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fharvestersofdarknessfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pic1.picturetrail.com/VOL129/612912/960667/11176020.ptp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter for Lady Ankhami Vlos'dAthiak</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>She picked up the parchment addressed to her, and made a face, noting the spelling of her last name. Tempted to just toss it in the fire she waked back to her room with that intention. <br>
