<br>
  Tullari , paced back and forth, it'd been a week and still no sign of an offer to free her ( half ) brother. She fumed , and paced some more. <br>
<br>
  Then she decided to take action, if her brother needed freeing, well then she'd just have to do it. Taking the box of family jewelry, thinking fond thoughts of her dead grandmother, who she hoped wouldn't haunt her for this. She set off from Qeynos , as an after thought she went back inside and changed into her best attire, though that was really just a less torn shirt, and leather breaches that had a few studs of moon ore on them for decoration.<br>
<br>
  She glared and walked forward with purpose, taking the  cow, and the jewelry to the shady part of Qeynos, were she ended up having to trade half of the jewelry to find out the location of the &quot;Harvesters of Darkness&quot;<br>
<br>
 More trudging, and pulling the cow along she crossed the expanse of the  hills of Qeynos, to the  rolling farmlands of the Karannas she made sure to stay on the road walking with this guard and that until she saw the spires, the ones that would take her to the town that  housed that evil evil person that had her brother.<br>
<br>
  Her knees knocked together as she walked up to the estate that homed the Harvesters. Looking at the  pikes the gate guards wielded she almost ran off. She wanted to say &quot; I'm here for my brother, send him out ! &quot; , what came out was &quot;eap &quot; <br>
<br>
  The steely eyed guard looked up and down the peasant girl with the cow , &quot; We don't give hand outs , what's your business here, before I have you run off. &quot;<br>
<br>
 She gulped , &quot; I'm  .. I'm  here to see Lady Ankhami , about personal matters. &quot;<br>
